<title>JAPAN: Toyota Motor to buy 76% stake in helicopter firm.</title>
<headline>Toyota Motor to buy 76% stake in helicopter firm.</headline>
<dateline>TOKYO 1997-07-15</dateline>
<text>
<p>Toyota Motor Corp said on Tuesday it would buy a 76 percent stake in helicopter operator Aero Asahi Corp from Seibu Department Stores Ltd for about 17 billion yen.</p>
<p>Further details of the agreement will be hammered out later this month, a Toyota spokesman said.</p>
<p>Aero Asahi, established in 1955, flies helicopters and carries out land surveys.</p>
<p>It posted parent revenues of 32.2 billion yen and parent current profit of 1.8 billion yen in the year to March 31.</p>
<p>The firm's total assets reached 34.5 billion yen as of March 31.</p>
